-- Barclays Hires Michael Gapen From Federal Reserve as Senior U.S. Economist
-- Matthew Brown
-- 2010-07-08T13:55:56Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-08/barclays-hires-michael-gapen-from-federal-reserve-as-senior-u-s-economist.html

          
          
             Barclays Plc hired  Michael Gapen  as a
senior U.S. economist from the Federal Reserve.  
 Gapen, who was a section chief for the Fed’s board of
governors, will focus on U.S. monetary policy and the effect of
financial markets on the economy, Barclays said in an e-mailed
statement today.  
 He will report to Dean Maki, Barclays’ chief U.S.
economist, the London-based bank said.  
